result.adr_address: 5 Staunton St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Lotus Modern Thai

reviews.text: The red curry is excellent.  Check this place out. My wife and I really enjoyed our meal there!

My favorite Thai in HK. Excellent spicy food (if you like really spicy), nice venue with open space on Staunton street and the escalator. You can enjoy the view of people passing by while taking advantage of the sunny weather refreshed by some good old style ventilators. 
Missing one star because they don't serve coffee and their wine is simply not good (But the choice of beers and cocktails makes up for it)
Edit (Nov 16): used to be my favorite Thai in Hong Kong. The cook changed. The food is absolutely awful. Still a good spot for drinks
Edit 2 (Jan 19): seems they got an excellent cook back. Now the food is back to it's best.
Edit 3 (Jun 19): good chef gone, menu seriously downsized to less dishes. Extremely slow service (More than 45min wait to get food...). Just pass.
Only went for a drink. Coke was way too expensive and it didn't look clean. Neither the tables nore the kitchen.
Worst bar in the area. Go to staunton bar across the street to have better quality of drinks and service
Reasonable price with quality food😎🤘

This was a great area for sightseeing and taking a walk. There are an amazing assortment of restaurants and stores along the way. We ate at a little hole in the wall Vietnamese restaurant that was absolutely awesome.

This neighbourhood has a couple of murals that are well known to tourists, (ex. The one pictured here as well as the brooklyn mural). It is a great place for taking photos; however, I would recommend for future visitors to arrive earlier to take pictures (11:30 am latest) because it will get pretty crowded at the murals after noon.

Good area in Hong Kong overall to go out and chill -whether you prefer that be over good food, drinks or both. Some places here also show sports games, and there are plenty of cuisines represented. Do prepare to spend a bit more, and getting around in the crowd here can be tiring, or nearly impossible if you have mobility restrictions.
Such a great vibe. Lots of great bars. Very western environment not what you would imagine HK to be like.
Soho is a little upscale part of LKF central. Most Western locals go here. You will have fun!

한참을 걷다가 비도 많이 오고 다리도 아프고 해서 잠깐 쉬어가는 생각으로 생맥주 한잔하고 나왔습니다. 물론 한국보다 비싸지만 여행지의 추억 값으로는 충분한 가격으로 기분좋게 한잔 마시고 좋은시간 보내고 나왔습니다.. 다음에 간다면 여기 대각선 건너편 바에도 가 보고 싶어요... 거기에 자리가 없어서 여기서 한잔한 거거든요...아... 사진에 있는 맥주는 별로였어요... 밀맥주치고는 냄새가 완번 별로...ㅋㅋㅋ
